description: On the evening of April 10,1996,400 lucky people witnessed the public re-emergence of Alice in Chains on MTV's "Unplugged" stage. The 13-song set highlights material from the band's albums "Dirt" and "Alice in Chains" and the acoustically-based EPs "Sap" and "Jar of Flies," plus a brand new song, "Killer Is Me." Song: "Nutshell," "Brother," "No Excuses," "Sludge Factory," "Down in the Hole," "Angry Chair," "Rooster," "Got Me Wrong," "Heaven Beside You," "Would?," "Frogs," "Over Now," "Killer Is Me"
